However, most of the cost comes from the 3D printing machines, which can be a large proportion of overall costs for a production run, alongside labour, materials, preparation and post-processing. The requirement for high-quality powdered materials also adds to the cost of 3D metal printing as they are more expensive than non-powdered metals in the same quantities.
